main event: Observation of three unidentified flying objects over China Lake, California on 5 October 1955.
interesting points: The observation lasted about 45 seconds., The source of the report was a civilian observer., The objects were described as luminous and flickering., There is speculation that the sighting could have been meteors or jets., The objects appeared to hover and their disappearance was instantaneous.
sighted object: three luminous objects in the sky
